 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Associate Director, GMP Quality Operations BioXcel Therapeutics Morristown, NJ Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Position Summary 
Reporting to the Sr./Exec Director of Quality, the Associate Director/Director GMP Quality Operations is responsible for providing Quality oversight of Bioxcelâ€™s manufacturing and testing network for BXCL-501. This role will be responsible for QA oversight of QC testing, material management, appropriate equipment maintenance, sample management, batch release, and environmental monitoring. The candidate will coordinate deviation/investigation management, OOS/OOT investigations, CAPA, and change control follow-up and implementation. The candidate must be on-site for Quality support of ongoing clinical development manufacturing, validation activities, and commercial manufacturing. The individual will be responsible for providing leadership guidance on and must be self-motivated, with a desire to succeed at the highest level, working with teams to oversee all GMP related activities associated with BXCL-501 and address any potential issues that may arise. 
 Position Responsibilities 
 Partner with QA colleagues, QC, Analytical Development teams, manufacturing teams, Regulatory, vendors, equipment vendors, suppliers, and facilities, to provide quality input, and review and approval (as needed), of key documents, including, but not limited to: MBR/specifications, Change control documents, Deviations, investigations, CAPAs, Deviations, Laboratory methods and validation reports, Testing specifications, Analytical results - Stability reports - Non-conformance reports; 
 Provide QA support for ongoing validation activities for equipment, facility, utility, laboratory, cleaning, sterilization, and process qualification and validation. Review and approval of method validation, process validation, and tech transfer (as required) â€¢ Performs disposition of raw materials, if needed; 
 Participates in regulatory interactions, which includes pre-meeting discussions, dossiers, and inspections; 
 Ensures that all personnel have adequate training, education, and experience to perform their GMP-related job function effectively; 
 Serves as a Quality liaison with internal and external customers; 
 Participate in the development of risk management control processes and support the development of the commercial Quality strategy for Bioxcel; 
 Support the development and enhancement of Bioxcel procedures related to GMP compliance, quality management systems, document management and control, annual product reviews, training, and raw material/product disposition;
  Support, as required, the implementation and maintenance of the electronic Quality Management Systems (as applicable), as well as development of key performance indicators and metrics to monitor effectiveness of quality as related to manufacturing, quality control, materials management, vendor performance, and others measures of quality, consistency, and reliability;
  Provide support and guidance for the resolution of complaints, investigations, deviations, CAPAs, change controls, and other quality systems issues; 
 Stays current with industry trends and methodologies relevant to GxP; 
 As needed, support therapeutic research & development, as well as discovery goals. 
 
 
Required Education, Skills & Experience 
Bachelor's degree with 10 years of experience in a regulated industry
 Must be on-site for Quality support of ongoing activities, as necessary
 In-depth knowledge of quality operations and compliance of clinical and commercial manufacturing
 Experience in deviation, change, and CAPA management
 Experience in Health Authority Inspections
 Excellent interpersonal skills, including team-oriented approach with ability to partner with others in fast paced, rapidly changing environment
 Significant experience in the generation, review, and monitoring of controlled documents such as SOPs, control test records, materials and product specifications, policies and other procedures as related to GxP compliance and operations 
Knowledge of business, manufacturing, and quality IT systems
 Experience in developing and using certificate of analyses, certificates of testing, and certificates of compliance as applied to areas of responsibility
 Quality Certification (i.e. CQA, CMQ, or CQE) 
